Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createPtnFeedthrough(25.10)                        createPtnFeedthrough(25.10)

Name
       createPtnFeedthrough - Creates a partition routing feedthrough object

Syntax
       createPtnFeedthrough

       [-help]

       <feedBox>

       [<layerId>]

       [-name <string>]

       Creates  a  partition routing feedthrough object. The object area keeps
       pins from being created on the specified metal layer. A dump file  with
       routing  obstruction  is created for the top level partition (done when
       saving the partition). You can use this command during partition floor-
       planning.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each createPtnFeedthrough parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man createPtnFeedthrough

       <feedBox>
              Specifies  the  coordinates   (x1  y1 x2 y2 ) of the feedthrough
              area.

              Data_type: rect, optional

       <layerId>
              Specifies the metal layer where pins are not to be created.

              Note: If<layerId> is not specified then by default  feed-through
              is created on all the partition layers.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -name <string>
              Specifies the name of the routing feedthrough.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The  following command creates a feedthrough object to block pins being
       generated on layer Metal5:

       createPtnFeedthrough 2353.8000 7123.000 2653.8000 8298.2000 5

